{"_id":"00Fn3EGcgYfLaKiD","name":"Forager","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You’ve grown up in the wild and are accustomed to foraging for food and extracting whatever nutrition you can from meager grasses, tough weeds, and scraggly plants in your home region, and know their properties regarding health. When in the wild, you may make a Challenging (D2) Survival test to find healing herbs. Each Momentum yields 1 Reload for a healer’s bag or 1 dose of medicine.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"0RoGMD4UpvjwoKAj","name":"Treacherous","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your homeland, and its folk, are unfortunately known throughout the Seven Empires for their unreliability and dishonesty, and adages are common identifying you — perhaps unfairly — as being untrustworthy. Persuasion attempts against those from other homelands are increased by one step of Difficulty, but any successful Persuasion test results in 1 free point of Momentum. If the test is made over an issue of money, you receive an additional +1 Gold instead of this Momentum.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"168knIFTnHnGD2dD","name":"Shoot for the Horizon","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learned to take shots at any range compensating instinctively for variations in weapon manufacturing, weather conditions, and other anomalies that could affect the trajectory of an attack. You can reduce the penalty for firing at a range other than the weapon’s optimal range by one step, to a minimum of 0.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"78"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Ranged Weapons","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Accurate)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"1Dc1fYi6XRlUoCiK","name":"Rugged","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>The rocky hills and desolate steppes are your home more than any civilized town or city, and you are far more comfortable sleeping in the open or in a desert tent than in a bed. Between adventures, you can perform your Upkeep when in the wild. When doing so, make a Challenging (D2) Survival test. If successful, each point of Momentum can reduce the Gold cost by 1. If unsuccessful, you must spend the full amount of Gold. The expense is depletion of supplies rather than hard coin.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"1TN7zquMKdjeN63B","name":"Saddle-Bred","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your people are horse nomads, and life in your tribe was entirely centered around horses. Not only were they transportation, but you also grew up wearing items of horsehide and leather, were weaned on horse milk, and ate horse meat when there was no other game. As such, the Difficulty of any Animal Handling test when dealing with a horse is reduced by one step, as well as any Survival test made when you are mounted or with a horse.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"1idcfNl6U7mtHhAD","name":"Obscure Trail","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know a variety of tricks to make it substantially harder for someone to follow you. When you suspect (or fear) that you might be followed, you may make an Average (D1) Stealth test. The Difficulty for any pursuer’s test to follow you is increased by one step, plus an additional step for each Momentum spent (Repeatable).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"86"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Stealth","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Camouflage)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"1kZ48ZBuV7are2y2","name":"Reaver","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your caste is known for piracy or raiding activities up and down the coast, against your own people, against neighboring countries, or everyone else. Your Reputation is increased by +1 when dealing with anyone with a nautical or pirate background, and you inflict an additional 1[CD] damage on Threaten attacks against anyone that has heard of you.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"1ovH6sRXcxTdo0z2","name":"Stage Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can believably fake combat with others, presenting no risk to the ones facing you. When using Parry to engage in such deception, any attack made gains the Nonlethal quality.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"75"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Parry","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Deflection)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"2dFbxucOrTRsWvgN","name":"This Will Hurt","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know that setting bones and tending to injuries will cause plenty of pain, and there’s little good that comes from being gentle when trying to save a life. Better that they suffer pain now and live to tell of it. When you attempt to treat a patient’s injuries, you may choose to reduce the Difficulty of the test by up to three steps. However, if you do this, you also inflict 2[CD] mental damage on that patient, plus an additional +1[CD] for every step of Difficulty reduced, as your swift and indelicate actions cause the patient intense pain.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"67"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Healing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Bind Wounds)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"2f9xTOgx3sV4nPks","name":"Garrulous","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have an ever-expanding range of transitory contacts. Any time you need assistance from other individuals, you may reduce the Difficulty to find a contact by one step per rank of Garrulous.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"83"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Society","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(A Modicum of Comfort)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"2qC1PZntWiFYHj3f","name":"True Understanding","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may pay 2 points of Resolve to gain 1 bonus Momentum on any Sorcery test other than tests to cast a spell. You may do this once per rank in this talent, paying up to 6 Resolve in this fashion.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"84"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Sorcery, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3CThzCYpUvUm34Oj","name":"Shipbuilder","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>The craft of shipbuilding is zealously guarded by the members of your caste, whether they be the hereditary shipwrights of the Vanir; the guilds of Argos, Shem, or Zingara; or the Stygian sect devoted to such labor. You add +1d20 on any Craft test to repair or maintain a watercraft.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3MmanaDjDT2LBnAI","name":"Barter Your Soul","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>By entertaining the dark forces, your patron introduces you to your patron’s own fell lords. The rituals involved are harrowing and sanity-destroying, but ultimately rich in knowledge. Gain one spell. Reduce your character’s Resolve permanently by X+2[CD], where X is the total number of spells you will know once you gain an additional spell from this bargain. Barter Your Soul can be taken multiple times, representing multiple deals to supernatural entities, selling your soul piecemeal, or selling fealty in the afterlife in terms of millennia of servitude.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"167"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Pact)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3NFnLJZV4FjXA9vX","name":"Resilient","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your physique is particularly sturdy and resilient. Whenever you suffer a condition that may be avoided by adding to Doom, you can reduce the amount of Doom you need to pay by your rank in Resilient, to a minimum of 0.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Resistance","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Stubborn as a Mule)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3dXqPWr5XfSDDCRg","name":"Clannish","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Blood, as they say, runs thick, and when dealing with those of your clan with the Command, Persuade, or Society skills, you gain 1 automatic success on any test instead of rolling. Additionally, when in your home community you count as having the Tradesman talent.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3xS4iayMLxhmbtkZ","name":"Might","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are able to perform feats of strength that seem at odds with your physique, due to a combination of training and expertise. On any test to lift or move an inanimate object, you may roll a number of bonus d20s equal to your ranks in Might, though the normal limit of three bonus d20s still applies.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"61"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Athletics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Strong Back)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"4EPUQvADPGZBkXyX","name":"Delver in the Dark","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have paid attention to the votaries of Skelos and know many secrets about dark forgotten places. When exploring old ruins, you may substitute Sorcery for Insight, Lore, or Thievery. Additionally, you may add 2 to Doom in order to substitute Sorcery for Athletics.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"83"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(True Understanding)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"4QXxetN8adedVtP0","name":"Sea Legs","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have been at sea for a long time, and are more-than-familiar with the swaying and shifting of the deck, so much so that you may even be a little out of sorts when on dry land. You no longer suffer any penalties caused by the random motion of being aboard a ship when taking any test. Additionally, you may substitute Sailing for Acrobatics, Athletics, or Resistance while onboard a ship or when using a rope.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sailing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sailor)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"4gSfSYvgf3Fp0eLs","name":"Dabbler","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Having studied many alchemical formulas, you are comfortable with making your own discoveries through experimentation. You are not restricted as to which petty enchantments you would make but doing so is very expensive. You must spend three times the number of reagents needed before making any alchemy test to build a petty enchantment for which you do not have the Master of Formulae talent.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"58"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Alchemy","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Alchemist)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"4veATJL3r0y6M9Nf","name":"Wealthy","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have squirreled away significant resources in longterm investments with multiple merchant families. Each rank of Wealthy grants 1 bonus Momentum for the express purpose of reducing the cost of any purchase, to a minimum of 1 Gold.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"83"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Society","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(A Modicum of Comfort)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"5h9C9g2hjgyMJJ0k","name":"Respected","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are treated with respect by the folk within your homeland, regardless of their personal feelings towards you. You may add +1d20 to any Society rolls made with anyone from your homeland who knows who you are and has heard of your family and is not of the same Social Standing as you. </p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"5nHn2Tpd5mL5UB3B","name":"Primitive","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Though the Seven Empires are ancient, your homeland is remote and slow to rise. Many of the touchstones of civilization — architecture, society, religion, craftsmanship — are woefully behind those of its rivals. Your connection to the wild is more profound, however. You may reduce the Difficulty of an Animal Handling or Survival test by one step by paying 1 Doom.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"64CzRDQKXKirWwg3","name":"Homesteader","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You’ll take the wide vistas of crops and fields over the cramped, stinking confines of a city any day. So long as you are in your homeland, you reduce the Difficulty of Survival tests by one. This may reduce tests to Simple (D0).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"20"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste(Farmer)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6KH5JBW3NdXcODrd","name":"Sharp Senses","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may re-roll one d20 when making an Observation test, but you must accept the new result.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"74"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Observation","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Observation, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6PZNX06eCwwNo9Bb","name":"Common Ground","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have a broad education that includes an understanding of history and culture from a variety of different perspectives. When interacting with an opponent, you may attempt an Average (D1) Lore test as a Minor Action. On success, you recognize within your opponent an element of common ground for discussion. Any Momentum from the Lore test may be immediately added to a Persuade or Command test, taken as a Standard Action.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"71"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Lore","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Scribe)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6f1W0wMoxTidRTwf","name":"Hunter","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You’ve lived with the wild as a constant neighbor, and know how to take from that environment what is necessary for survival. When in the rural parts of their homeland, the number of successes required for any Survival tests you attempt is reduced by 1, even if this reduces the Difficulty of the test to Simple (D0).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"15"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Bossonian Marches, Cimmeria, Gunderland)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"74zkrq8Q0Pbj7zLF","name":"Fickle Fortune","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are always gambling with fate and fortune, and willing to take a chance on a better reward. You may spend 1 Fortune point to gain three bonus d20s on a skill test, rolled normally (the normal limit of three bonus d20s still applies), instead of simply specifying a single d20 with a '1'∩┐╜ for a result. This choice can be made on a case-by-case basis: 1 Fortune point is spent for each instance.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"90"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Fortune","talentType":"other","prerequisites":"Talent(Make Your Own Luck)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"81BW2vcb8PZJ2GJk","name":"Decadent","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your homeland may not be as ancient as others in this age, but its wealth and resources have enabled its citizens to thrive for so long that their interests become focused on pleasure and aesthetics more than sustenance. They have not known hardship in decades, and debauchery is commonplace. When in your homeland, your Upkeep costs are increased by 2CD, but for every effect rolled you automatically recover 1 additional Wound or Trauma (your choice), free of charge, up to your total.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"82ttQnF2pKh7tWKP","name":"Animal Healer","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Any time you are called upon to make a Healing test upon an animal, you may instead substitute your Animal Handling skill. You may also substitute your Animal Handling skill for Healing tests upon humans, but you must increase the Difficulty of any such tests by one step.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"59"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Animal Handling","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Faithful Companion), Expertise(Animal_Handling, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8VEUMv1tkQfyVPZr","name":"Savage Court","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>With civility being a new addition to your homeland, it is difficult to know when the old ways will rise to the surface. In any scene within your homeland, you can make a free Challenging D2 Lore test. Each point of Momentum gives you a general idea as to how easily it would be to overturn the civility of the moment and cause savage old emotions to rule the day.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"15"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Keshan, Hyperborea, Darfar, Khitai)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8dFTNSXwWMEQx0Pa","name":"Pact","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your character selects a second patron. This is a permanent addition, a new master that must be kept appeased. In return for such appeasement, the patron teaches you one spell or petty enchantment. The second patron can be the same as your first patron, in which case you have a redoubled pact, but this patron cannot be used more than twice. After the second rank with a particular patron, there is little else you can offer that patron, and thus you must seek another if you wish to learn additional ranks in this talent.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"167"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sorcerer)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":2},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8h7DARoULFLbn2ad","name":"Stubborn as a Mule","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have gone through grievous injuries and survived truly epic quantities of ale and mead. You have learned how to face down the seemingly insurmountable, and rely on your physical stamina to do so. When already suffering from an injury, you may substitute your Resistance skill for Discipline, if desired.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Resistance","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Hardy)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"97sW9RbMlI7i5wiK","name":"Sea Raider","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>The Difficulty of all Sailing tests made in your homeland's waters are reduced by 1. This can reduce tests to a Difficulty of Simple (D0). Additionally, the Difficulties of any Athletics tests relating to swimming are similarly reduced.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"15"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Argos, Zingara)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"99iyoTkiyxYh07PS","name":"Grappler","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know that a mobile foe is a dangerous one, and the easiest way to stop someone moving is to grab hold of them. After making a successful melee attack, you may spend 1 Momentum to gain the Grappling quality on an unarmed attack.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"73"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Melee","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(No Mercy)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9IQs0iGzwzHBRbIH","name":"Vagabond","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>The road is more home to you than any town or city ever has been. Whether a nomad by choice or necessity, you can reduce the Difficulty of Survival tests by one, so long as you are on a maintained road. This may reduce the Difficulty of tests to Simple (D0).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"21"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste(Escaped Serf/Slave, Merchant)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9IarKIOaCJ0qWMTu","name":"Deft Blade","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You wield a blade as if it were an extension of your arm. Whenever you make a melee attack, any Momentum spent or points added to Doom to add bonus d20s to the Melee test adds two dice instead of one, though the normal limit of three bonus d20s still applies.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"73"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Melee","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(No Mercy), Expertise(Melee, 2)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9cASTKw76wTQ9Rwl","name":"Blessed","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are particularly resistant to supernatural attempts to manipulate your perceptions, beliefs, and mental processes. Any time you attempt to resist supernatural powers that target your mind, you may re-roll any d20s that did not generate at least one success, though the second roll stands. Further, each d20 that you roll a 1 on will cause a single Complication for the attacker.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"65"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Discipline","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Healthy Superstition), Expertise(Discipline, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9do2JRN0aNVJkypO","name":"Sixth Sense","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may re-roll one d20 when making an Insight test, but you must accept the new result. In the event of an ambush, you gain 1 additional bonus point of Momentum. If the Insight test was requested because of sorcerous or otherwise unnatural phenomena, the gamemaster must reveal this.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"68"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Insight","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Insight, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9nC7Mrqh6d7p9bEK","name":"Honest Corruption","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>In a land of corrupt merchants and honest thieves, you have gained a sixth sense about those who are likely to betray you. When interacting with a non-player character for the first time, you can make a free Average D2 Thievery or Counsel test to gain a general feel for the trustworthiness of the non-player character.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"15"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Zamora)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9vcOKRdXmilZgIms","name":"Remorseless","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are willing and able to tell any lie that you feel is necessary to overcome an opponent’s social defenses. When lying to an opponent, you gain one additional d20 per rank of Remorseless to your Persuade or Command test.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Persuade","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Haggler)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9xGanxki53jP9jEP","name":"Ancient Bloodline","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Whenever you fail a Personality test, pay the GM 1 Doom and add a d20 to your test (unless you already rolled 3d20).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Bloodline","talentType":"bloodline","prerequisites":"AncientBloodline()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"A27kd7IoUFzbUjkx","name":"Lucky Charm","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You carry a trinket, talisman, or some other small item of superstitious worth, which must be specified when this talent is purchased. It may not be anything so large that it cannot be carried in one hand. While this item is on your person, whenever you spend a Fortune point, roll 1cd. If an Effect is rolled, you gain the benefit of the Fortune point, but the Fortune point itself is not spent and returns to you.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"90"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Fortune","talentType":"other","prerequisites":"Talent(Make Your Own Luck)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"A5EH0eflPowuGqcC","name":"Of Saddle and Bow","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Hyrkanian riders are renowned for their facility while on horseback, with stories of these horse archers reaching far and wide. As one of these riders, you count as having the Hunter talent so long as you have a horse and bow ready for use. You can also reduce the Difficulty of any Animal Handling test by 1, even if this reduces the Difficulty of the test to Simple (D0).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"15"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Hyrkania)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"AB3QuGu7lBGNGPic","name":"Everlasting Sorcery","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You must permanently sacrifice 1 Fortune point in order to house a spell within an inanimate vessel. The cost for doing this is ten times that a regular enchantment in both offerings and treasure. Preparing the spell is a Minor Action, needing only a rudimentary understanding of sorcery (Sorcery Expertise 1). Once invoked, the spell uses its Momentum as decided by the caster preparing the vessel. The spell can be invoked once per scene, although there is no limit to the number of spells a vessel might contain, assuming you have made the requisite Fortune point sacrifices.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"167"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Enchanter)","category":"","cost":800,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ADPJyZUdPINLqsnW","name":"Sabotage!","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are able to identify the problem with any broken item or structure, or to recognize a vulnerability that could be used to cause such a break. You reduce by one the Difficulty of any Craft test to perform repairs or maintenance. When an Exploit Action is taken using the Craft skill, Sabotage! grants bonus Momentum equal to your Craft Skill Focus.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"64"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Craft","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Journeyman)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"AIqRbpDz5R7EtPyt","name":"Indefatigable","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are tireless, able to press on when others would falter. Whenever you would suffer Fatigue, you may ignore it by adding a number of points to Doom equal to the Fatigue suffered.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Resistance","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Hardy), Expertise(Resistance, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Anw0a0Qre9CDf6tZ","name":"Sentry","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You learned at a young age that the watchful eye subsists on little rest. So long as you have had a total of four hours of sleep within the last two days (either one four-hour stretch or multiple short rests), you suffer no penalties for sleep deprivation when making Observation tests.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"21"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste(Herder, Warrior)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"AvB0MwKS9bP7Ox8U","name":"Hunter","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learned to anticipate the movements of prey. When making a Survival test to track a creature or group of creatures, you may spend 2 Momentum or add 2 to Doom to find a shortcut or other way of intercepting the creatures being tracked. You may also substitute Survival for Stealth when attempting to ambush creatures being tracked.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"86"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Survival","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Tracker)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":2},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"BE50PEB4bZBOMGIe","name":"Alone at Sea","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>When a ship is damaged on the water, it is often unable to reach a port where repairs can be made, requiring a temporary solution. You are familiar with the methods of repairing a ship in the short-term so that it can survive long enough to undergo proper repairs. You may substitute your Sailing skill for Craft when attempting repairs on watercraft. However, those repairs will only last for a scene, plus an additional Scene per Momentum (Repeatable), before proper repairs are required.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sailing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sea Legs)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Btb0CAr2D9aGG6Xj","name":"Polyglot","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are a master at understanding languages. You speak the active languages of all the locations you have traveled to, and will immediately learn the active languages of anywhere you visit. Learning the language(s) costs 1 Fortune point, which can be spent at any time during the visit.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"69"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Linguistics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Accent), Focus(Linguistics, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"BwWvT8nst8NgKHnD","name":"Body Language","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are a master at understanding people. You can speak with any living person so long as there is no immediate distraction that would prevent communication, at which point the Linguistics skill must be used as normal. This communication requires a Standard Action but no test is needed. You can also substitute Linguistics for Insight.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"69"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Linguistics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Polyglot)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"CFMLQVJAZaaTAx2F","name":"Perfect Memory","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have a knack for recalling information, even if it was irrelevant at the time. You can make an Observation test to investigate any area you’ve been to, even if you are not in that location any more. You cannot change any of the physical features of the area, meaning that your memory is limited to what you actually experienced. For example, if you didn’t look behind a tapestry or open a door, you have no idea what they conceal. However, if you also have the Ransack talent, it should be assumed that you opened/ closed all doors and looked at the scene from multiple points of view.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"74"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Observation","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sharp Senses)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"CbxLtFXIvBPnQi9G","name":"Haggler","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are particularly proficient at striking a bargain, either to obtain goods or favours. After making a Society test to purchase an item, you may roll a Simple (D0) Persuade test and reduce the cost by 1 by spending 2 Momentum (Repeatable).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Persuade","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Force of Presence), Expertise(Persuade, 2)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Chss0T38FqGEc5AE","name":"Subject","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are a subject in good standing to a lord or king. While subject to their laws, the taxes you face are much less than the more expensive taxes others experience. Whenever you pay Upkeep within your homeland, you can reduce the amount of Gold the Upkeep costs by one.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"21"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste(Crafter, Farmer, Herder, Petty Nobility, Priesthood, Warrior)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"DAn227knXU9DioJH","name":"Marksman","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learned to perform ranged attacks with great precision. You may spend a Minor Action before attempting a ranged attack, putting a little more time and effort into your attack. When you do this, you gain 1 additional Momentum to use for the attack.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"78"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Ranged Weapons","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Accurate)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"DLLIzO0QMmPfoxv5","name":"Spotter","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are familiar with discovering enemy positions and communicating this back to your leader. When assisting in setting up or seeking out an ambush, or when assisting an artillery crew as a spotter, you may add your Warfare dice pool rather than only a single d20.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"91"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Warfare","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Strategist)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"DtJfsQsffpaQiLEb","name":"Iron Will","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have survived countless challenges and are prepared to face even more. You don’t cry out when struck or startled, and you quickly rebound from Stress. Rather than having to choose a particular stress when you take a Recover Action, you recover both Vigor and Resolve, regaining the same amount of each (two points, plus two per Momentum spent). In addition to this you can add 2 points to Doom in order to perform the Recover Action as a Minor Action. If you use this option, you do not get to re-roll Cover dice, as outlined in the Recover Action.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"65"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Discipline","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Courageous)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"EGZboAIU3Rs2sj4Q","name":"Politically Savvy","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are familiar with the philosophies, styles, and motivations of various political entities. When interacting with an opponent, you may attempt a Simple (D0) Lore test as a Minor Action. One Momentum is enough to recognize the foe’s significant political and personal affiliations, based upon their apparent mannerisms and actions. Additional Momentum provides more detailed information.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"72"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Lore","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Scribe)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"EUXVnIdkL0iD8Dmq","name":"Strong-Arm Tactics","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You recognize others’ limitations and can easily exploit them. When attempting to intimidate an opponent, you are able to recognize the most effective strategies to use. You gain one additional d20 to any Persuade or Command test per rank of Strong-arm Tactics. Further, you gain Piercing X on your Threaten attacks, where X is equal to your ranks in Strong-arm Tactics.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Persuade","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Force of Presence)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"EgRSDRpij0UAhUQT","name":"Spy","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can perform the Ransack talent without leaving tell-tale evidence of the search. To notice that a search has been undertaken, you must engage in a Struggle with the character that used this talent upon the space, gaining bonus Momentum equal to your Observation Focus.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"74"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Observation","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Ransack), Expertise(Observation, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"EszyNzhaPyUvPDo1","name":"Healthy Superstition","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Some superstitions are just common sense, and you hold many of those beliefs. This superstition allows you to stand firm in the face of the unnatural, even if doing so would seem foolhardy. When facing supernatural threats, you are empowered by this belief. When a supernatural threat manifests, you may spend one Momentum (Immediate, Repeatable) to immediately gain 1[CD] Morale Soak, which lasts until the end of the current scene.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"65"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Discipline","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Courageous)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Ez4EK5ts0YlDnD6E","name":"Inspiring Leader","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are an inspiring presence to those who follow you. All of your allies and subordinates gain 2[CD] Morale Soak while they can see or hear you. Any characters who are within close range gain 4[CD] Morale Soak instead.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"62"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Command","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Captain)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FQWXwek4bMTR21lt","name":"Reputation","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have gained something of a reputation, and are often recognized by friends and foes alike. Each rank of Reputation increases your Renown by 1.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"83"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Society","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(A Modicum of Comfort)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FvMFC9OvuznpKH3Y","name":"Friends in the Maul","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Once you have lived in any place for any length of time you pick up a variety of hangers-on and informants. In any location where you have had downtime, you have at least one useful contact on tap. All skill tests made during downtime gain a d20 so long as the skill test does not involve combat of any kind.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"82"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Society","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Garrulous), Expertise(Society, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FyZaPFkudOAj0Ww2","name":"Know the Signs","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have personally dealt with the effects of the supernatural, and recognize the signs of its activity. Whenever you are in the presence of a person or object that was affected by supernatural abilities within the last six hours, you may attempt an Insight test, with a Difficulty equal to the number of hours ago the person or object was affected. On success, you can recognize the taint of the supernatural. By spending 2 points of Momentum, you can identify the specific powers in use.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"68"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Insight","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Pierce the Veil)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"G9W8nx9OsLfCsmQe","name":"Seducer","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are particularly adept at seducing others. When attempting a seduction, you gain two additional d20s to your Persuade test per Momentum spent or Doom generated, instead of one, though the normal limit of three additional d20s still applies.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Persuade","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Naturally Charming)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"GEduD3itFWSg5g2y","name":"Faithful Companion","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You recognize the needs of your animal companions and are rewarded with devotion. When this talent is purchased, you must nominate a single animal you own. This becomes an animal companion. Generally you can control your companion, though the gamemaster may guide its behavior in some instances. Each additional rank allows you to nominate one additional animal companion. Whenever you succeed at a Survival test to find food, water, or shelter, you automatically find adequate food and shelter for your animal companion(s) as well, without needing to spend Momentum or increase the Difficulty of the task. In addition, when in combat, if you have one or more animal companions within reach, you gain a bonus d20 on your Defend Reactions made against melee and threaten attacks.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"59"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Animal Handling","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Born in the Saddle)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"GzUMj4Q3wMleYqhV","name":"Nimble as a Cat","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Whether a career thief or just naturally graceful, you can leap extraordinary distances or suffer falls without harm. When making an Acrobatics test to jump or leap, reduce the Difficulty by one step for every rank of Nimble as a Cat. This may eliminate the need for the skill test if the result is reduced to Simple (D0). In addition, for each rank of Nimble as a Cat you gain 2 additional Armor Soak dice when suffering falling damage.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"56"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Acrobatics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Agile)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":2},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"H38ej4JqjNQ9DOEk","name":"Mason","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have been apprenticed to a skilled mason, and have learned the specialised and highly-valued skills necessary to oversee the construction of important buildings: temples, castles, palaces, and similar monuments. When overseeing a team of laborers during a construction project, you may use your Craft skill instead of Command. With a Standard Action, you can find or create heavy cover adequate for one character. Given suitable time and resources, you can create this level of protection for an entire zone.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"64"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Craft","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Barricade), Expertise(Craft, 2)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"HHq0CU4dZmJXOgSq","name":"Riposte","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>The instant after an attack is the moment when the attacker is the most vulnerable. After successfully making a Defend Reaction using the Parry skill, you may immediately add 1 to Doom in order to make a Melee attack against the foe you just parried. Momentum remaining from the Parry Action may be carried over to this Melee attack.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"75"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Parry","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Deflection)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Ieh4a3WIpinfmJSa","name":"Crippling Blow","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know how to place your blows to deal crippling harm. After making a successful attack, you may add 1 point to Doom in order to make the attack particularly effective. Add a number of additional damage dice to the attack equal to your Observation Focus. Each time this ability is used in a single scene, the cost of using the ability increases by 1: the first time adds 1 to Doom, the second adds 2, the third adds 3, etc.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"74"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Observation","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Battlefield Perception)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"J9IvFllHDxtDznfA","name":"Message Runner","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Couriers and message runners must get through the harshest conditions, across land that even goats would balk at. They learn to recognize the environment and to move naturally in response to it, taking advantage of the terrain’s effects. For each rank of Message Runner, you can reduce by 1 the Difficulty of any Acrobatics tests made to overcome obstacles, hindrances, hazards, and other forms of difficult terrain.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"56"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Acrobatics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Agile)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":2},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"JZr8mI2lix3fxoYI","name":"Chirurgeon","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have encountered a variety of sicknesses, plagues and injuries, and have learned many effective ways of treating these maladies. You can attempt an Average (D1) Healing test to identify the best course of treatments for any patient you encounter. On a success, you are able to prescribe a suitable remedy. You may spend Momentum to have the necessary treatments on hand, though the cost in both money and time is subject to the gamemaster’s discretion. You are a figure of authority and can substitute Healer for the Command skill. If you command another character to assist you or to act in your stead, that character can reroll a single d20 of their own Healing test. Given suitable downtime, you can completely heal the injuries of others.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"67"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Healing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Apothecary), Expertise(Healing, 2)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"JhK44GWsot4QQUN4","name":"General","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have become particularly adept at coordinating the actions of soldiers. When leading an army or unit of warriors in battle you can substitute Warfare for Command, Counsel, or Persuade. In addition, you can create a retinue (warband, squad, etc.) of dedicated and highly-loyal warriors of a size equal in number to your Warfare Focus times your rank in this talent. For example, if you have General 2 and Warfare Focus 2, you can have up to four warriors in your retinue. The warriors in your retinue must be chosen prior to combat, must be dedicated followers who have trained with you, and must be within earshot to gain any benefits. This benefit does not apply to other player characters, even if they are under your control. These are considered to be Elite Minions, whereas normal soldiers or warriors are normal Minions.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"91"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Warfare","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Strategist)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"KBayC5FP26ozgQp9","name":"Born in the Saddle","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have spent a lifetime in the company of animals and can recognize personality quirks and identify potential sources of distress. On any Animal Handling test where you generate at least one success, you may immediately roll a number of bonus d20s equal to your ranks of Born in the Saddle. Any successes generated on these additional dice are added to the initial success total, and Complications on these additional dice may be ignored.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"59"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Animal Handling","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Animal_Handling, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"KE7iF0SnEvjt1Z2D","name":"Tracker","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can recognize all the signs of passage, from the subtle to the obvious, and have become particularly adept at following a target. When attempting a Survival test to track a creature or group of creatures, you may reduce the Difficulty of the test by one step for every rank of Tracker.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"87"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Survival","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Born Wild)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"KzTyxV6Ks5y37Sie","name":"Rescue the Innocents","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Instead of using the ability from Witch, prior to combat you can attempt a Simple (D0) Insight test to evacuate innocents from the scene. For every Momentum spent, you can earmark three chosen non-player characters and ensure that they get to safety. These non-player characters cannot be targeted by combat unless the gamemaster pays three points of Doom for each attack.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"68"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Insight","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Witch)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"LabN3k0PLqgoemFG","name":"A Modicum of Comfort","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have a legacy of wealth or substantial funds available to you, and can leverage old debts into sustaining you. Reduce your Upkeep by 1, to a minimum of 1.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"82"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Society","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Society, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MC0GIhGwwwcahsLJ","name":"Life Eternal","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may petition the scribes of your dark masters, beseeching them to disregard your mortal form, sparing you the chastisement of time and the degradation of the self and soul. You will not die, no matter how old you get or how many injuries you suffer.These hurts will affect you, however. You will feel them just as much, and they will heal as normal. If your body is completely destroyed, you will be an insensate, unmoving, unending presence, a fate only spared to you if you have the Astral Wanderings spell. It is rumored that some have bargained for eternal youth as well, drinking life deeply from victims ensnared in dark rituals. For some sorcerers, seeking out the means of learning this talent is the sole ambition of their enfeebled immortality.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"167"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Barter Your Soul)","category":"","cost":800,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MFiDynH8FA6RQBlJ","name":"Accent","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are familiar with the idioms and speech patterns of a broad range of different populations. You know not just how to speak a language, but how to speak it in a fashion that sets a native speaker at ease, often even utilizing a local dialect. You can substitute Linguistics for Persuade.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"69"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Linguistics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Traveler's Tongue)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MPtKndyiOmT4EFJP","name":"Protective Superstitions","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>When involved in a Struggle to resist the effects of a spell, you gain one bonus Momentum per rank of Protective Superstitions.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"84"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(True Understanding)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MVM7MW32MhtZpFA0","name":"Strong Back","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are a magnificent example of human physical prowess, all-too-frequently abused for this ability. For any Athletics test that generates at least one success, you generate one additional success for each rank of Strong Back. Further, your Encumbrance limit is increased by 1 for each rank of Strong Back.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"61"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Athletics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Athletics, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MWoWA7dw5mW2FjLq","name":"Lightning Reflexes","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have a natural sense for when your life might be endangered. When involved in a struggle to resist being surprised, you gain 2 bonus Momentum.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"56"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Acrobatics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Savage Instincts), Expertise(Acrobatics, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MakXLz5hJlCqBCFQ","name":"Wave-Harvester","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your family has always taken its wealth from the sea, whether in the form of fishing or diving for the sea’s bounty. When you attempt to dive for pearls, gather a harvest of saleable fish, etc. in familiar waters, you gain the Hunter and Tradesman talents.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MbTtX2TMTJhe96If","name":"Perfect Ambush","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have such mastery of stealth and subterfuge that you can perform an ambush with little-to-no preparation. When you perform an ambush, you can voluntarily make the ambush harder to pull off, and in doing so make it almost impossible to detect. When you attempt an ambush or surprise, you may increase the Difficulty of your Stealth test by one or two steps. The Difficulty of the enemy’s Observation test to spot the ambush increases by two steps for every step of increase you accepted.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"86"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Stealth","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Master of Disguise)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MmdY1ZScL6zg05X1","name":"Devastating Bombardment","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learned how to get the greatest effect from siege weaponry, using shots to shatter morale as well as masonry. After making a successful attack with a siege weapon, you may spend 2 points of Momentum to unleash a Devastating Bombardment. A Devastating Bombardment forces all creatures within Close range of the attack’s target to attempt an Average (D1) Discipline test or suffer mental damage equal to the attack’s damage rolled. Additionally, any Momentum spent to add damage to the Devastating Bombardment adds 2 points of damage rather than 1.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"90"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Warfare","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Ballistics), Expertise(Warfare, 2)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NB0lmBSPhr6WaRs3","name":"Sheltered","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You led a remarkably sheltered existence, buffered by family and servants against the rigors and dangers of the outside world. The prestige of your family means that you find many willing to pay for your room and board, so long as you are suitably grateful upon future visits. Whenever you enter a new town or city, you may seek out shelter from those willing to support you; these people pay your Upkeep.However, they are liable to ask for further compensation — either in Gold, or in the form of a favor — at some later juncture.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"21"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste(Petty Nobility)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NTBzwynoHwlkCkvq","name":"Respectable","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Though you are not particularly wealthy and have no inherited title, your caste is nonetheless held in high regard. Within your community, you may reduce the difficulties of any Command, Counsel, Persuade, and Society tests by one step, and you may reduce the cost of Upkeep by 1 Gold in addition to any modifications from Renown or Social Standing.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NWUKVljtQU1hJ4kT","name":"Charge!","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are particularly adept at riding mounts, even those not used to combat. When riding a mount of any kind, the mount is considered combat trained. When riding a horse outside of combat, you can reduce the Difficulty of any tests by one step.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"59"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Animal Handling","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Born in the Saddle)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NcA8pHXHXANpejxt","name":"Crowd Pleaser","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have become adept at gauging your attacks to create more spectacular results that are less lethal than they appear. After successfully hitting with a Melee attack, but before rolling for damage, you can reduce the damage of the attack by up to 3[CD]. You gain 1 bonus Momentum for each [CD] of damage reduced.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"75"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Parry","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Stage Fighting)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"OI8xfzFyJOTxYZN1","name":"Navigation","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learned to navigate watercraft through the many hazards of the sea. You may ignore any penalties to the Difficulty of a Sailing test incurred by situational hazards, including harsh weather, magical impediments, and similar dangers.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sailing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sailor)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"OOD8DE2XDCqMovKg","name":"Blood on Steel","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You do not hesitate to bloody your weapons. When rolling for damage with a melee attack, you may spend one Momentum in order to add the Vicious 1 quality to the weapon, or increase the weapon’s Vicious quality by 1 if it already possesses the quality.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"73"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Melee","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(No Mercy), Expertise(Melee, 2)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"OhvyO1Gq4m4UOvua","name":"Killing Strike","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your strikes are deadly, making corpses of all who cross you. When you inflict 1 or more Wounds as a result of a melee attack, you may spend 2 Momentum in order to inflict an additional Wound immediately. Against a mob or squad of enemies, this additional Wound may be applied to another member of that mob or squad.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"73"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Melee","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Blood on Steel), Expertise(Melee, 3)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Oultbdf3Vm29ha0L","name":"Apothecary","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are well-versed in treating poisons. You can attempt an Average (D1) Healer test any time you encounter a poisoned or drugged patient. On success, you are able to identify both the poison or drug and the antidote necessary to relieve its symptoms. You may spend Momentum to have the antidote at hand, though the amount required is subject to the gamemaster’s discretion, based upon the rarity and toxicity of the poison or drug. You can use the Healing skill instead of Alchemy or Animal Handling when treating or procuring venoms.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"67"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Healing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(A Little to Ease the Pain)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"P8bNr6gN0fyASgQ6","name":"Born Swimmer","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are as comfortable in water as you are on land. You can reduce the Difficulty of any swimming test by one step per rank of Born Swimmer, and can ignore any penalties for acting in water.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"60"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Athletics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Strong Back)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"PLOSvktorgjaYwvr","name":"Calming Oratory","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can speak to people and calm any situation. When making Persuade tests to convince someone to engage in conversation or to avoid violence, you may substitute Counsel for Command, Discipline, or Persuade. If a Struggle emerges from this attempt, the opposing side gains no bonus Momentum for having greater numbers. Once violence has been prevented this talent does not help with further negotiation.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"63"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Counsel","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(An Ear to Listen), Expertise(Counsel, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"PYjV7ALZWnJXXZn8","name":"Sorcerer","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your character’s eyes are open to the horrible realities of the cosmos. Gain 1 spell and reduce the character’s resolve permanently by 0+[CD]2.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"84"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Patron), WeedOfSorcery(2)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Pa3i1wjqlZNvB1as","name":"Guardsman's Eye","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are very familiar with the way a crowd would normally act, and recognize actions that are unusual. When dealing with places full of people — even if the people are not organized — you may substitute your Command skill for any Observation or Insight tests that deal with the crowd or the area. You may also use Command to resist against Thievery tests in a crowded area.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"62"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Command","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Captain)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"PkmE5SAFGU7bdo9c","name":"Seafarer","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are a reputable sailor with a name known in many ports. You can add 1 to Doom in any port to find someone who will vouch for you, including ports you have not yet travelled to. For the duration of the stay, this allows you to substitute Sailing for Society and grants a bonus d20 on any tests using Sailing in place of Society. If you are asked for a favor by another sailor at any time during your stay, you must grant it, or the effects of Seafarer can no longer be used for that stay.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sailing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sailor)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"PsdZBFH5crU0OPEn","name":"Hyperliterate","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Those with the Hyperliterate talent go beyond the simple literacy of the everyday scribe. They have studied multiple languages equal to their literacy focus and while unable to speak them in any meaningful way can read and write them fluently. Should the character later gain the Polyglot talent, the languages they gain from Hyperliterate add to that talent as well. </p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"QXPwxas5cwGcvQqC","name":"Explorer","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Many ply the waves in search of blood or gold. Some seek adventure upon the waves. You, however, look to the ocean horizon as a place of possibility. You and your family are navigators, and have always sought to explore and chart the seas and expand the knowledge of your immediate coast. Whenever attempting an Observation, Sailing, or Survival test while in unfamiliar waters you can reduce the Difficulty by one step.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"QYmXST0mSdlJWkPZ","name":"Call of the Sea","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have always looked to the sea as your destination, your home. You are more comfortable on the deck of a ship than on the streets of towns, and the great and limitless frontier is where you find yourself most at peace. As such, you have an intuitive understanding of the sea and the folk who travel upon it. You can re-roll any failed d20 for Insight or Command tests made against anyone with a naval or ocean-going background (at the gamemaster’s discretion).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"QYs23mlKJhsch6WV","name":"Reader of the Book of Skelos","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your mind has been corrupted with detailed knowledge of places and deeds both foul and terrible. When using the Ritualist talent to assist another character, you may spend Momentum to buy bonus d20s to add to your roll for the teamwork test.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"84"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Ritualist)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"QZTuhCG1WmNbhIuY","name":"Impervious","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have been injured before, and have faced something more grievous than what just happened to you. When you suffer a Wound, you may pay 1 Fortune point to ignore that Wound entirely.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"78"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Resistance","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Just a Scratch), Expertise(Resistance, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"RCoAQycJD8qFDt2q","name":"Naval Discipline","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Whether part of a tradition as organized as the naval fleets of Argos, Zingara, Shem, or Stygia, or the corsairs of Kush and the Black Coast, your caste have traditionally served at sea, and view the sea as a battlefield. When at sea, you gain 2[CD] non-stackable Morale and Cover Soak when fighting alongside at least one other character with this talent that has not suffered any Wounds.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"RTL8fc6tEwEIHN9X","name":"Voice of Jhebbal Sag","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Wild or tamed matters not to you: all animals are kin and to be afforded due respect. Any time you attempt to direct an animal to take an action that goes against its instinct or training — including instances when the animal is in service of another — any Momentum spent or Doom generated to add bonus d20s to the skill test add two d20s to the dice pool instead of one, though the normal limit of three bonus d20s still applies. In addition, any Momentum spent to obtain information using an Animal Handling test (based on interpreting an animal’s behavior) grants you one additional question. While this is not actual speech, the connection with the animal is uncanny.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"59"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Animal Handling","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Eyes in the Forest), Expertise(Animal_Handling, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"RUlOAX4QYKQvmtcB","name":"Living off the Land","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are particularly capable of finding the necessities of life. When attempting a Survival test to find food, water, or shelter, each point of Momentum spent (Repeatable) provides these necessities for two other creatures (allies, tame animals, etc.). If you are in your own homeland or some other territory you are extremely familiar with, the basic Difficulty of Survival tests to find food, water, and shelter is reduced to Simple (D0), and every point of Momentum spent (Repeatable) finds these necessities for three additional creatures, rather than two.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"87"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Survival","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Born Wild)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"RdGnASvkfcyK4qnK","name":"Death Dealer","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are a proficient killer, relying on trickery and misdirection. When armed with any weapon that has the Hidden quality, you may substitute Stealth for your Melee and Ranged Weapons skills, and increase the damage of the weapon by +1[CD].</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"85"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Stealth","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Many Blades)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"RqT0ubeJ4GRBAlAB","name":"Armorsmith","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have the knack for repairing armor in the field; making do with whatever is available to repair your armor and that of your allies, even when resources are scarce. When repairing armor away from proper tools and materials, you may add 2 points to Doom in order to attempt a repair on a single hit location’s armor, without the use of materials.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"64"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Craft","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Journeyman)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"RsWKNlQQe5JK2TRJ","name":"Artillerist","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learned how best to operate siege weaponry. When making an attack with a siege weapon, you may re-roll a number of damage dice equal to the number of Warfare talents (and ranks in them) you have acquired. The results of these re-rolls must be accepted.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"89"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Warfare","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Strategist), Expertise(Warfare, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Rsv88ooTXekyuwFg","name":"Bind Wounds","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may re-roll one d20 when using the Healing skill, but you must accept the new result.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"67"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Healing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Healing, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"S6hRQc4bwIeabJGj","name":"Regimented","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You’ve grown up surrounded by soldiers, part of a garrison troop, whether stationed your whole life on the frontier or from inside the great kingdoms and recently assigned. You may reroll any failed d20s when attempting Society or Command rolls with military non-player characters but must accept the results of the second roll. Additionally, your Upkeep cost between adventures is halved if you are quartered in a military barracks or with soldiers assigned to a garrison.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"S9pxOB6W8m8Vnq3g","name":"Tutored Warrior","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can study human foes to learn their weaknesses, drawing them out in combat to see how they react, and thus, learning how to exploit those moments when they are unintentionally defenseless. As a Standard Action, you may attempt a Daunting (D3) Parry test to learn one particular enemy’s patterns and weaknesses. For the remainder of the scene, you may re-roll a single d20 on every Melee or Parry skill test made against that enemy.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"75"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Parry","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Deflection)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"SZiM6A9v9wPbBBek","name":"A Cryptic Ear","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have a knack for spotting and solving word and number ciphers, even those hidden in plain sight. So long as you are fluent in the language spoken, the Difficulty of any test to decipher the hidden meaning is reduced by one step. In addition, you can add 1 to Doom in order to reduce the Difficulty of the test by one step further. This may eliminate the need for a test, if it becomes lower than Simple (D0).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"69"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Linguistics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Traveler's Tongue)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"SnOatRghKcwN4dj4","name":"Master of Disguise","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know how to impersonate others, whether to blend into the background or to appear as a specific person. When you succeed at a Stealth test to create a disguise, you gain bonus Momentum equal to the amount of Momentum generated on that test (in essence, every point of Momentum generated by the test is doubled). In addition to this, if the disguise is to impersonate another, you may substitute your Stealth skill for Persuade or Command.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"85"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Stealth","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Living Shadow)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"TEKDyY356pa5BVfI","name":"Trick Shot","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are an extremely precise shot. You gain one bonus Momentum on ranged attacks, though these may not be used to increase the attack’s damage and may not be saved in the group pool.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"78"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Ranged Weapons","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Shoot for the Horizon), Focus(Ranged_Weapons, 3)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"TII0CqNF7FlyiYFt","name":"Sullen Obedience","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Living as a second-class citizen has made you uniquely adept at seeming to follow orders while remaining your own master. Any test made to resist domination, social or magical, is one step of Difficulty lower than normal, to a minimum of Average (D1).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"TIud7lch2Cd2DkLl","name":"Battlefield Perception","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>During combat, you may choose one enemy and make an Average (D1) Observation test as a Minor Action. If successful, you can determine how much of the target’s Stress remains, and how many Harms the target is suffering from. For one Momentum (Repeatable), you may choose one additional foe.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"74"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Observation","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Scout), Expertise(Observation, 2)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"TL3QaE4Vxu9rgzMp","name":"Enduring","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>By tying your character’s spells to the ephemera of the mortal world, you have begun learning how to give them breath. With this talent, all of your spells and petty enchantments gain 1 extra Momentum to be used solely for the spell’s duration.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"167"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sorcerer)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"TRxnUX9CoHgw7pu2","name":"Iron-Skinned","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are so used to taking injuries that it now takes an impressive amount of damage to actually hurt you. You increase your Armor Soak on all locations by 1, and you still benefit from this Armor Soak if you are not wearing armor on that location (even if the armor was sacrificed).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Resistance","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Impervious)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"TeUkHHLEZpo8hFJt","name":"Appraisal","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have robbed many people, and over time learned the difference between valuable items and those that merely look valuable. You instinctively know the difference between real treasure and fake baubles and know to forgo lesser rewards for greater ones. When looking over valuable items to determine their worth and provenance, you may substitute Thievery for Insight or Lore. Further, when using the Easy Money talent, you may gain one additional Gold by adding 2 to Doom instead of 3, and you may use this benefit twice on any given criminal act.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"88"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Thievery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Easy Money)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"TvyU9ae21jfifu1v","name":"Minions","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Individuals under your authority become extremely loyal to you, perhaps even willing to sacrifice themselves. Any time you come under attack and have a non-player character minion under your command within Reach, that minion may generate one point of Doom. In return, one of your minions also immediately attempts a Protect Reaction. These non-player character minions do not need to be the same, but both must be under your command.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"62"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Command","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Commanding Men)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"U3y7tcMZmIBBRaDq","name":"The Enemy of My Enemy","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have come to recognize the reasons why an opponent is acting in a particular way, and can use that to dissuade them from acting. You may substitute your Lore skill for Command, Counsel, or Persuade when making a test against an opponent whose motivations you understand.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"72"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Lore","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Know Your Enemy)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"UEoNk8HKmNXGe8h8","name":"Untamed","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your robust and wild nature makes even your greatest failures sometimes feel like wild successes. Once per session, when you roll Consequences on a test, you gain an equal amount of Momentum from the roll as well.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"UuaeTmCRRBLbcJ7Q","name":"Pierce the Veil","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have a knack for recognizing the subtle cues of supernatural ability. Whenever you are in the presence of the supernatural or beings with unusual powers — particularly if you are not aware of them — the gamemaster should call for you to attempt an Average (D1) Insight test. On success, you recognize that the other being (or presence) has supernatural abilities, and may spend 2 Momentum to identify the type of abilities. This test should be made even if the target does not have any active abilities.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"68"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Insight","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sixth Sense)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"VYG2eLhMHjNpIIYc","name":"Conqueror","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>With this talent, you have learned how to bring your retinue (generated with the General talent, below) to bear with explosive force; any warrior in your retinue adds a bonus d20 to all Melee, Parry, Ranged Weapons, and Warfare tests. Warriors in your retinue no longer need to be within earshot to gain the benefit of your leadership. As with the General talent, this benefit does not apply to other player characters, even if they are under your control.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"90"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Warfare","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(General), Expertise(Warfare, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"VioDJ58oR6dcMvok","name":"Naturally Charming","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have a warm personality and a winning smile. People trust you. A successful Persuade test yields 1 point of bonus Momentum per rank of Naturally Charming.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Persuade","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Force of Presence)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"W3MSZHrSiaxHNT1v","name":"Connected","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>The wealth, rank, and name of your family precede you everywhere you go, opening doors closed to most people. With a successful Society check, you can gain access to the best individual to help you with a problem, no matter how busy or important they might be. In your home city, this test is Average (D1). In other lands, it is Challenging (D2). Within hostile territories, it is Daunting (D3). Keep in mind that with power comes enemies. Your gamemaster will use any complications resulting from these tests accordingly.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"W4QCBgcahDElkk5z","name":"Thief","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>After years of dealing with the criminal underworld, you have a basic familiarity of how to interact with this segment of the population. You may use Thievery in place of Society when dealing with criminals. When you generate at least one success on a Persuade or Lore test to relate to or interact with the criminal element, you may immediately roll one additional d20 and add the result to the skill test.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"88"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Thievery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Thievery, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"W5ouWVVeVJKYIPZN","name":"See the Soul","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>While you might not literally see the human soul, you can intuitively relate your alternate senses to the physical world. When dealing with mortal humans you may substitute your Insight skill for Society and Thievery.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"68"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Insight","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sixth Sense)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"WXyzIpxKjY0XojNa","name":"Fisher","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Some part of your youth was spent on a fishing boat, or diving for fish in the shallow waters near your home. When making Survival or Swim tests in or adjacent to the water, you may add an additional +1d20 to your rolls. Every point of Momentum on the Survival roll provides enough food to feed an additional person for one day.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Wg83Ys9AtJKdqOY6","name":"Underworld Lore","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have listened to your elders and know many tales of amazing scores and terrible calamities. When considering a theft of any sort, you may spend 1 Momentum (Immediate) to know the fate of the last thief who attempted a similar act, and any precautions the target is likely to have taken since. Additionally, whenever studying the activities, traditions, taboos, and histories of a region’s criminal underworld, you may substitute Thievery for Insight, Lore, or Observation.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"89"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Thievery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Thief)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"WmtjAPOIEngvMO8k","name":"Witch Hunter","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have turned your knowledge of the unnatural to the practical concern of saving your own life. In a combat where there is at least one sorcerer or unnatural creature on the opposing side, you may attempt a Daunting (D3) Sorcery test as a Standard Action. If successful, you gain 1[CD] extra Cover Soak against your foe’s attacks and powers. Momentum increases this Soak by +1[CD] (Repeatable).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"84"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Protective Superstitions), Expertise(Sorcery, 2)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"WmxMEz3S4dc91K5J","name":"Priest","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are an ordained priest in one of the land’s many cults. Wherever in a town or city your faith has a presence, you may spend time amidst the faithful before travelling again. When Carousing, if you do not have sufficient Gold to pay your Upkeep, you may turn to your order for support. If you do so, you are required to donate all remaining Gold you have. If you attempt to cheat your order out of any of the Gold they are owed, you are expelled from the order and lose access to this talent until restitution or some sort of penance has been made (at the gamemaster’s discretion).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"20"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste(Priesthood)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"XaXjg4Njlstkcka9","name":"Blot Out the Sun","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>When you target a mob or gang with a ranged attack, the Secondary Target Momentum spend deals full damage to each additional target, rather than half damage.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"77"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Ranged Weapons","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Hail of Arrows)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"XdIMOmLiwVS4aIgL","name":"Old Salt","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are a veteran ship-hand: you’ve weathered storms, survived pirates, and struggled through the foulest misfortune. Through all of it, you’ve learned to trust your own skills and those of your shipmates, and learned to spot the wide range of expertise available on a ship’s crew. While onboard a ship with a reasonably-sized crew, you may add 1 to Doom in order to substitute your Sailing skill for any skill, except for Alchemy or Sorcery.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sailing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Alone at Sea), Expertise(Sailing, 2)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"XeJh6PhYQqX4WsoZ","name":"Desert-Born","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your homeland is a vicious and arid one, harsh and indifferent to its inhabitants. When in the desert, the number of successes required for any Survival test you attempt is reduced by 1. This can even reduce tests to a Difficulty of Simple (D0), usually an automatic success. However, when attempting Survival tests in areas offering the Winter-born talent, you must achieve 1 additional level of success.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"15"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Stygia, Zembabwei, Iranistan, Afghulistan)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Xem7zKy6NV0XfAK9","name":"Master of Formulae","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Most alchemists work extensively with a specific formula, which becomes second nature. More exacting measures become the standard. When selecting this talent, you must also select a specific type of petty enchantment: blasting powder, lotus pollen, etc. When using this petty enchantment, you may attempt higher Difficulty tests to increase the power of the particular enchantment.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"58"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Alchemy","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Alchemist, Sorcerer)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"XqHBvetFRGUBpVgX","name":"Exiled","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Some past crime, oath-breaking, or disagreement sent your family into exile, and you can never return or hold a place in the society that is your own. You must spend 2 additional Gold when Carousing within your homeland, but for all other purposes your Social Standing is treated as if it were 2 higher in the Carousing phase.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YISV9Svn3gXroya0","name":"Commanding Men","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You speak in such a way that even those who do not know you or fully understand your language recognize your charisma and persuasive abilities. You can substitute Command for Linguistics or Persuasion tests.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"62"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Command","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Heed My Words), Expertise(Command, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YP7spZwx919ONU71","name":"Murder in the Eyes","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are a savage up close, where your foes can feel the wet heat of your breath and see the savagery in your gaze. When attacking an opponent that does not have Guard, add +2[CD] to your damage roll.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"73"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Melee","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Grappler)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YmRldu4z0E8BTP1j","name":"Tradesman","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have passed apprenticeship with a tradesman or within a guild. While your talent may be mediocre or worse, at least you have a fallback plan. When Carousing, if you do not have sufficient Gold to pay your Upkeep, you may offer your services to a tradesman or to a guild in order to cover your Upkeep. However, you may not take any other actions during that period of Carousing.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"21"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste(Crafter, Merchant)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Yuwl6Ia6XVEawaZ5","name":"Assassin","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are practiced in the art of murder, and taking lives no longer carries any emotional weight. When rolling damage with a melee weapon that has the Hidden quality, you may spend 2 points of Momentum in order to count every dice in the pool as an Effect, instead of whatever was actually rolled. Additionally, you gain +2[CD] Courage Soak.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"85"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Stealth","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Death Dealer)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZFnV5OgqxWBTltQb","name":"Walk In, Walk Out","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Committing a crime is easy: getting away with it is harder. Through practice, you have learned how to avoid notice by blending in with the crowd. You may substitute your Thievery skill for Stealth when attempting any criminal act.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"89"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Thievery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Master Thief)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aEojPKri18Ezam43","name":"Living Shadow","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are adept at using terrain effects and social cues to remain unnoticed by observers. When attempting to remain unseen or unnoticed, you gain bonus Momentum equal to the number of your rank in Living Shadow.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"85"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Stealth","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Stealth, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bG9EFmMC9BQNq0Dc","name":"A Little to Ease the Pain","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>In your past you worked with extremely limited resources, and have learned to take full advantage of them when available. When using medicine from a healer’s bag, each load adds two d20s to the Healing test, instead of the usual one, though the normal limit of three bonus d20s still applies. In addition, if you have access to narcotics or alcohol you can make a Daunting (D3) Healing test to convert a dose of either into a dose of medicine.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"67"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Healing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Bind Wounds)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bLjv2S0foLlUaVp6","name":"Journeyman","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have passed apprenticeship and passed its trials. When making a Craft test, you may either roll one extra d20 or spend 1 Doom to reduce the Difficulty of the test by one step, to a minimum of 0.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"64"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Craft","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Craft, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bU7P46fQu4Yyg8Rz","name":"Accurate","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>When making an attack with a ranged weapon, you may re-roll a number of damage dice equal to the number of Ranged Weapon talents (and ranks in those talents) you have acquired. You must accept the result of these re-rolls.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"77"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Ranged Weapons","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Ranged_Weapons, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bYMNjg1hz2uKGZ9X","name":"Ransack","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are adept at thoroughly searching an area quickly. The search is obvious to any onlookers and any who examine the area searched, with a Difficulty determined by the size of the area to be searched. Searching within Reach requires an Average (D1) Observation test, while searching within Close range becomes a Challenging (D2) test. With a successful Observation test, you identify all of the clues that you currently consider important in that area. Ransack takes a Standard Action and can be attempted multiple times.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"74"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Observation","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sharp Senses)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bYukVBL6XZ4tbCvc","name":"Burglar","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have made a career of entering the towers, homes, and palaces of the wealthy. You’ve experienced tall walls, cunning traps, and strange locks, and have developed a broad range of different techniques to overcome them all. Any time you attempt to enter or leave a property with larceny in mind, you may add 1 to Doom in order to substitute Thievery for any other skill except Alchemy or Sorcery.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"88"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Thievery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Walk In, Walk Out), Focus(Thievery, 2)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bZh8TDtsQIYXI88h","name":"Jaded","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have repeatedly observed and suffered cruelties, and have built up a tolerance to mental suffering. Increase your maximum Resolve by one for each rank of Jaded.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"65"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Discipline","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Courageous)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"csanmAFIfuGsZ856","name":"Cosmopolitan","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your homeland has many visitors and people dwelling within it, all with different customs and tongues. When speaking with a non-player character that also has the Cosmopolitan talent, it is assumed that you each possess enough of each other’s languages in common that you are considered fluent when speaking with one other.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Aquilonia, Khoraja, Brythunia, Nemedia,Khauran)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"dCxSWJfP1TxUIw1o","name":"Remedies and Rewards","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know various natural or traditional remedies for illness and sickness that can be found in the wild. When outside of the city, you may substitute your Survival skill for Healing or Alchemy. Additionally, when travelling through the wilderness, you may make a Challenging (D2) Survival test once per journey. Each point of Momentum achieved provides 1 poultice for use in treating wounds.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"87"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Survival","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Risks), Expertise(Survival, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"e5E0ftM3OtHaFZO4","name":"Avoid Danger","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You recognize various environmental risks and know how to mitigate them. You may substitute your Healing skill for Survival for the purposes of avoiding hazards.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"67"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Healing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Bind Wounds)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"eMJlmMisVH4ft9cP","name":"Resplendent","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your home kingdom is akin to a strutting peacock, its arts and culture so refined and ostentatious that you stand apart from other lands. The quality of craftsmanship, clothing, and architecture in your homeland stands head-and-shoulders above those of others. Any equipment you begin with is worth an additional +1 Gold per item, and you may add an additional +1d20 when performing any Craft test.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"eMVPfww9Ni80fsve","name":"Courageous","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may re-roll a single d20 on any Discipline test, though the second result stands. For every point of Discipline Focus, you gain 1 Courage Soak.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"65"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Discipline","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Discipline, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"eby4x3cD3bP2Mwdz","name":"Salt for Blood","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your family has had a long tradition of ocean-going and sailing, and you’ve grown up on the shore, spending as much of your time on or in the water as on land. Swimming tests are reduced by one step of Difficulty.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ef0pgj5OnpTqyDB0","name":"Sophist","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have become known for your wisdom and council, and many are happy to hear you speak. You may substitute Counsel for Persuade or Society.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"63"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Counsel","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Quiet Wisdom)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"enKknMVg4g7kkul1","name":"Many Blades","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You always carry at least a dagger concealed somewhere. Even if you lose all your weaponry, you can add 1 to Doom and produce a concealed dagger as a Minor Action.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"85"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Stealth","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Living Shadow)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"eoVjQ2NV4neFLwCk","name":"Ritualist","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are well-versed in the sorcerous arts, understanding enough to assist true masters with their work. When performing teamwork tests or rituals using the Sorcery skill, you can assist with 2d20 rather than the normal d20 teamwork provides.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"84"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(True Understanding)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fIbdRKKm5i6TTL2Q","name":"Risks","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are familiar with various environmental hazards presented by the wilderness. Choose one environment when this talent is purchased, and any time you travel within a particular kind of environment you may attempt an Average (D1) Survival test. On a success, you are able to avoid all implicit dangers, potentially avoiding dangerous encounters. Each point of Momentum may be spent to protect one of your allies from these same risks. Further ranks in this talent add new environment types. Possible environments are: Arctic, Coastal, Desert, Jungle, Mountain, Forest, Plains, Steppes, Subterranean, Urban, or another if permitted by the gamemaster.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"87"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Survival","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Born Wild)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":11},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fXayxtgH0Ql40pKz","name":"Agile","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may re-roll one d20 when attempting an Acrobatics test, but you must accept the new result.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"56"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Acrobatics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Acrobatics, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fhgm5xx7CXpxFukS","name":"Enchanter","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learned to bind spells into treasures. Every success or Momentum stored requires one offering and a single “named” treasure of value equal to the total Momentum of the spell. These offerings can be any item of portable wealth such as jewels, golden statuettes, or similarly valuable objects.Weapons, armor, and the like are never counted as offerings, but adornments on such items can be added to them to fulfill this function. The named treasure must be something of relative fame and uniqueness, with a specific name (or names) it is known by, and might even be considered an item of legendry, coveted by many. Preparing this spell is a Minor Action, needing only a rudimentary understanding of sorcery (Sorcery Expertise 1). The spell is otherwise a normal spell, and the treasure becomes non-magical once the spell is cast. Discovering whether an item or person has been enchanted is a Challenging (D2) Sorcery test for a character with this talent. This Difficulty is increased to Dire (D4) for those who do not have this talent.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"167"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Enduring)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fqwaY6KXGgPICfBz","name":"Better Lucky than Dead","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Whenever you suffer a Wound or Trauma, you may spend 1 Fortune point to ignore it entirely. In this case, the Wound or Trauma simply does not happen, though the attack inflicts damage normally in all other regards.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"90"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Fortune","talentType":"other","prerequisites":"Talent(Make Your Own Luck)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ftGFVd4Cw3qqkBKc","name":"Hardy","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>When making a Resistance test, you may re-roll any dice that did not generate a success on the initial roll, but you must accept the new result.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"78"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Resistance","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Resistance, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fw4UxTrTgUXdvSko","name":"Gilded","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>In a land where gold is commonplace, you have learned to spot those pretending to have wealth. In every scene, you can attempt to make a free Average D2 Thievery or Craft test to gain a general feel for the wealth of a particular non-player character, or even the relative worth of an environment.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"15"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Ophir, Punt, Turan, Vendhya)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fzAgLtqComLIew8x","name":"Barricade","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learnt to put up barricades or small structures quickly and efficiently. If you take a Standard Action to create a barricade, you can find or create light cover enough for one character. If given suitable time, you can find or create protections for an entire zone.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"64"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Craft","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Armorsmith)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"g22tl28OdCQAxAko","name":"Labor of Love","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Master Smiths can create truly beautiful works. When you have access to your tools and create a labor of love, you can use any bonus Momentum granted by Master Smith to increase the attractiveness of your work. This offers little functional difference to the finished item itself, but will increase your wealth and influence. With Labor of Love, you can use Craft in place of Society tests and gain 1 extra level of Renown for every rank of Master Smith.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"64"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Craft","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Master Smith)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"g2oCu8EPhR7rw8dC","name":"Traveler's Tongue","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You gain one additional language fluency for every Linguistics talent you possess.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Linguistics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Linguistics, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"gdeVqvH7zv0vCrVR","name":"Ear of the King","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know the best way to raise awareness of an issue with the proper authorities. When attempting to spread a message across a large group of people, or even a region, you can substitute your Society skill for Command. In addition, the Difficulty for all skill tests dealing with civic figures is reduced by one step, so a minimum of Simple (D0).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"82"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Society","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(\"Wealthy\", 3), Talent(\"Reputation\", 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"h0CsiQJVYCgLZ9hJ","name":"Sailor","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are an experienced sailor, accustomed to river, sea, or ocean. You may re-roll one d20 when making a Sailing test, but you must accept the new result.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sailing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Sailing, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"h2LLp0FTCgcHFEco","name":"Human Spider","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have spent a significant portion of your life in an environment that involves a great deal of climbing, often in the presence of sheer drops. You are very comfortable acting in these environments and never suffer from vertigo or fear of heights. In addition, you never suffer a penalty for a lack of climbing equipment and may reduce the Difficulty of any climbing test by one step.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"60"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Athletics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Strong Back)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hwN4QH8InQd9xR9f","name":"Born Wild","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can reduce the Difficulty of any Survival test to find food and shelter by one step, to a minimum of Simple (D0). Born Wild is factored into the difficulties of all Survival talents.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"86"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Survival","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Survival, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hx29uVEPesEpr32h","name":"Demon Slayer","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learned how to most effectively harm and kill unnatural beings. When using the Witch Hunter talent, you can spend 1 Momentum to add Vicious 1 to your weapons (or increase the Vicious quality by 1 if your weapon already has the quality) against any sorcerers and unnatural entities present in the scene.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"84"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Witch Hunter)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"i7Ok3HJvZ0GWWPkR","name":"Motivate","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have a way of hastening the recovery of your allies, quickly and effectively restoring their determination and morale. When treating another character to recover their Resolve, you gain 1 bonus Momentum per rank of Motivate, which must be used to recover additional Resolve.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"63"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Counsel","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Quiet Wisdom)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"iLn4cKnUktyb1MlM","name":"Quick Release","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are able to ready a shot almost as soon as you’ve loosed the previous one. When using a ranged weapon with the Volley quality, you may spend a Minor Action to increase your rate of attack, allowing you to spend two Loads, gaining a bonus d20 and +1[CD] damage for each Load spent.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"78"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Ranged Weapons","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Accurate), Expertise(Ranged_Weapons, 2)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"iWbZfvbD0b5zw3TO","name":"Migrant","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Life in the steppes is hard enough, but it becomes especially onerous when dealing with the nearconstant threat of soldiers from Shem, Stygia, Khauran, and especially Turan, bent on exterminating the nomad tribes that threaten their supremacy. Furthermore, not all nomad tribes view themselves as allies, and raids between camps are all-too-common. You’re able to break camp in a moment’s notice, and transport yourself rapidly away to a new location, no matter how arduous. Whenever you or your mount suffer Fatigue from extended travel, you may make a Challenging (D2) Resistance test. Each point of Momentum reduces the Fatigue by 1 point.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"j4PbKi7fDmAG1kQF","name":"Wise Veteran","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have become proficient in making certain that the actions of a group are well-coordinated. Any time you are involved in a teamwork test — even if you are not the leader for the test — all characters involved may choose to re-roll any die on the initial roll that results in a failure. They must accept the results of the re-roll, even if they are worse than the initial roll.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"62"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Command","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Guardsman's Eye), Expertise(Command, 2)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jDl4wWuy6D1Rv92w","name":"Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You’re able to perform particularly well, telling stories and sagas in a way that enlivens them and engrosses your audience, whether a single companion or a room full of drunken warriors. Whenever you’re using this talent, you can substitute your Lore skill for Society tests, and you may reduce your Upkeep by 1 Gold if you choose to entertain your host, if applicable.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jT8qEFuI15vRehIT","name":"Uncivilized","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You’re uncouth and lack civilized manners, and those of more civilized societies will think poorly of you upon first impression. As a result, you suffer one step of Difficulty in Social tests when dealing with people from more civilized countries. On the other hand, your Upkeep cost is reduced by 2 Gold, as you are accustomed to roughing it and making do with what you have.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jjBOu3L0LmgBWlFx","name":"Scrounger","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Having spent your life in the ranks of camp followers taught you how to survive. Yet, it is not the sort of survival that involves living off nature’s bounty, but rather the scrap that civilization leaves behind as the mercenary cavalry’s hooves stamp them flat as autumn leaves. You can find things to eat, use as tools, and trade where others see only junk. Treat this as the Living Off the Land talent, but only in places where the civilized exist or existed. This includes the mercenary company and the camp followers, or tross, as the mercenaries disdainfully call them.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jkez03BZzdL2crNa","name":"Camouflage","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>It is important for you to remain concealed, but at times it is also important that your allies and any equipment they may be using also go unseen. You can apply your Stealth skill result to a number of other creatures or large objects equal to your Stealth Focus plus your ranks in Camouflage.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"85"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Stealth","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Living Shadow), Expertise(Stealth, 2)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jr6gFGPD8FSXcncN","name":"Smell Out Sorcery","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Instead of using the ability from Witch prior to combat, you can attempt a Challenging (D2) Insight test to sense any sorcery, whether a sorcerer, summoned creature, ruin or artifact within medium range. However, this test is highly inaccurate and its consequences may target innocent victims.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"68"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Insight","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sorcerer)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jsHsi4YecGja2lgY","name":"Enterprising","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>The untamed frontier holds no fear for you. You may also choose to “rough it” between adventures, forgoing any Upkeep cost entirely, but during such a period any equipment is not restored and you cannot upgrade or seek out new equipment, cultivate Renown, find new contacts, etc. You do not roll for any Carousing events when roughing it, though the gamemaster may wish to introduce or select an event appropriate to your circumstances.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kbrboTQOOGSci2P1","name":"Master Thief","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may re-roll one d20 when making a Thievery test, but you must accept the new result.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"88"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Thievery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Thief)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ke3rCRD789dCjbPt","name":"An Ear to Listen","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You listen patiently to the problems of others, and few can dispute that hearing your voice steadies the nerves and stills doubts. When making a Counsel test to recover Resolve or treat Trauma for another character, every point of Momentum paid or point of Doom generated to add dice to the Counsel test provides two d20s instead of one, though the normal limit of three bonus d20s still applies.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"62"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Counsel","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Quiet Wisdom)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kgHMARaSPBpQKn2Q","name":"Patron","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have obtained a patron, who will teach you the arts of sorcery. You may now purchase the Sorcerer talent and can begin to learn spells.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"84"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"WeedOfSorcery(1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lHszea3JhbKm2TR5","name":"Iron Grasp","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You never drop or surrender an object unless you wish it. You are immune to the Disarm Momentum spend, and cannot drop your weapon(s) as a result of Complications.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"61"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Athletics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Human Spider, Born Swimmer)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"leFTCSMSUZDVVM6L","name":"Powerful Friends","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know many powerful people in positions of significant authority. When selecting this talent, you gain a number of Powerful Friends equal to your current Society Focus. You must specify the type and allegiance of each influential contact, but must also obtain the gamemaster’s approval for that selection. You may attempt a Daunting (D3) Society test to ask the selected contact for a favor. On a success, the contact responds with resources proportionate to their level of importance and the nature of the request. Any goods provided must be returned within a reasonable time limit: a period decided by the gamemaster but usually at the end of an adventure. You can attempt one such skill test during each period of downtime or in-play visit, taking a suitable amount of time to pleasantly broach the topic. Powerful Friends may be purchased multiple times, with each purchase establishing new contacts equal to your current Society Focus.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"83"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Society","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Friends in the Maul)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"m3oNUmGjipl9ZWEG","name":"Savage Dignity","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Despite your barbaric upbringing, you have a fierce sense of pride in yourself and your lineage. You cannot be dominated or cowed easily. You may roll an additional d20 for any test to resist being intimidated, persuaded, or impressed by a “civilized” person. This is usually a Discipline test, but can extend to Personality-based tests such as Command or Society.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"m8TsDGK3QQEKJIqs","name":"Deflection","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know the importance of keeping your weapons up and ready to defend. When making a Defend Reaction using the Parry skill, you can reduce the number of points added to Doom by 1, to a minimum of 0. This stacks with the weapon’s Parrying quality.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"75"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Parry","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Parry, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mKfQTWKe4eGLAqcp","name":"Play the Part","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are so familiar with foreign cultures that you have learned to impersonate the members of a broad range of cultures. This includes style of dress, speech, and other mannerisms. When attempting to make use of a disguise, you may substitute your Lore skill for Stealth.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"72"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Lore","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Common Ground), Expertise(Lore, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mkqENBYkQkfiT0xH","name":"Child of Jhebbal Sag","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>While not literally one of the offspring of this primitive animal god, your character is nonetheless accepted naturally by animals. Any time you encounter a new animal, you may attempt an Average (D1) Animal Handling test as a Minor Action. On a success, the animal immediately considers you to be a friend. If the target is a guard animal, it does not alert its handlers to your presence.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"59"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Animal Handling","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Voice of Jhebbal Sag)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mtXWgOM3VdZ9ZQ6Z","name":"Anatomist","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know the human body like no other and can exploit this in many ways. When making a Healing test to treat injuries, you can reduce the Difficulty of any test by one step, to a minimum of Average (D1). In addition to this you may add +1[CD] and the Vicious 1 quality to any melee or Threaten attack you make, as your knowledge of the body makes your cuts and your threats alike all-the-crueller and more specific.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"67"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Healing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(This Will Hurt)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"nKTqRrFfynBNnfxv","name":"Two Tongues","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are a master at expression and can transmit a private message at the same time as a public one. You can take two Speak Actions at the same time. For others, cracking your spoken code is a Daunting (D3) Linguistics test, though for the expected recipient it is an Average (D1) Linguistics test to understand the message.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Linguistics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(A Cryptic Ear), Focus(Linguistics, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"nfvf3OW3cfl3rai4","name":"Social Chameleon","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>It is one thing to be convincing for a minute, it is another to be convincing for a lifetime. When impersonating a different social caste, this talent lets you substitute your Persuade skill in place of Animal Handling, Craft, Insight, Society, Survival, or Thievery, though only when convincing others that you have this expertise. Any practical application of the skill that requires actual knowledge relies on your existing relevant skill, if any.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Persuade","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Remorseless)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"nohCAliqZSHJluW3","name":"Sea-Trader","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Due to your familiarity with the coastal trade routes, you’ve developed a network of friends and allies in the various port cities, and know your way around such environments. In coastal settlements, you gain the Tradesman talent. When engaging in trade, you gain an additional +1d20 when rolling for Persuade or Discipline tests to get the best deals.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"nuCfFUf3HUXZLy8t","name":"Winter-Born","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Born in a place of deep winter and intense cold, often spanning the entire year, you are accustomed to frigid climes. When in wintry environments, the number of successes required for any Survival test you attempt is reduced by 1. This can even reduce tests to a Difficulty of Simple (D0). However, you must achieve 1 additional level of success when attempting Survival tests in areas offering the Desert-born talent.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"15"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Nordheim, Vanaheim)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"o9OQhEGaMkJ8CFLz","name":"Curse","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You must permanently sacrifice 1 Fortune point to house a spell within a living creature, usually to inflict some negative effect or condition upon the desired subject of the spell. The resource cost for doing this is twenty times that of a regular petty enchantment. You must have a trigger that will activate the spell’s effects, which may cost additional Momentum. The amount of Momentum should be determined by the gamemaster based on how subjective or narrow the focus of the trigger is. The more specific, the more expensive the Momentum cost should be, and the more general and outside human intervention, the less expensive the spell will be. For example, “When the moon turns full” is specific but is general and predictable, with no human intervention whatsoever, so it would cost no extra Momentum. A trigger such as “When the name Aktur Ashmal is spoken” would be an easily controllable event, and could cost as much as 3 additional Momentum. Once the curse’s effects are complete or have otherwise passed, the spell is done.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"167"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sorcery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Barter Your Soul), Talent(Everlasting Sorcery)","category":"","cost":1000,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ocN3OPkdmDKU6PnO","name":"Sage","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have an impressive amount of knowledge at an academic level. When performing research on any topic covered by the Lore skill you may reduce the Difficulty by one step per rank of Sage. This may eliminate the need for the test.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"72"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Lore","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Scribe)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"okU04jHJQBQqdJlx","name":"Comforting Lies","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know that often, the greatest reassurance comes from denial, and while it is not always the best way to give counsel, it can be valuable in dire times. When you successfully treat one or more Traumas another character has suffered, that character may add 3 points to Doom; the Traumas treated are now healed instead of simply being treated.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"63"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Counsel","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Quiet Wisdom)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"plh8ax6hsWTuoy7Q","name":"Brutal Brawler","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can ignore the effects of the Improvised quality, and increase the damage of the basic Improvised Attack by +1[CD].</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"60"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Athletics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Pugilist), Expertise(Athletics, 2), Focus(Melee, 2)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ptTPseRXqnPF22vM","name":"Survivor","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Deprivation has been all-too-common in your life. When you are deprived of obvious sources of food and water, you reduce the Difficulty of Survival tests by one. This may reduce tests to Simple (D0).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"21"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste(Outcast)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"q360OrOpwJrliZMD","name":"Easy Money","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are particularly astute at recognising profitable opportunities such as picking pockets, short cons, and other minor crimes. You may substitute your Thievery skill for Observation on any tests that are related to committing a crime. In addition, whenever you steal or otherwise obtain money by illicit means, you may add 3 to Doom in order to gain 1 additional Gold from that particular crime (and only one additional Gold).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"88"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Thievery","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Thief)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"qBLCpyDfj1xpC5ao","name":"No Mercy","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>When making a Melee attack, you may re-roll a number of damage dice equal to the total number of Melee talents (and ranks in those talents) you have acquired, if desired. You must accept the results of the re-rolls.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"73"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Melee","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Melee, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"qTg0TbPW2Vt8suwr","name":"Pastoral","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Decades or centuries of relative peace have left the people of your homeland optimistic and full of joy, even when faced with deep adversity. Once per play session, you may think back on happier times and take a Recover Action as a Minor Action, restoring Resolve only.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"qwn5A6F4hbmqpE0p","name":"Savage Instincts","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are constantly in motion and difficult to hit with ranged attacks. If you use a minor or standard action to move during your turn, any ranged attacks targeted against you increase in Difficulty by one step.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"56"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Acrobatics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Agile)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"r75MCZrhWEESN7zy","name":"Adaptable Combatant","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can adjust your fighting style to suit a range of circumstances. When making or defending against an attack, you may increase or decrease the Reach of your weapon by 1. A weapon’s Reach may not be reduced below 1.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"73"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Melee","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Deft Blade), Expertise(Melee, 3)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"rCuWHBI6gqMc4OCQ","name":"Faded Glory","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Millennia of affluence, corruption, and ennui in your homeland has bred an entire civilization inured to the pleasures of the flesh and mind. No debauchery is too much for the people of your land, nor is any excess new or shocking. When you make a test to resist, enjoy, or employ some form of decadence, you can voluntarily fail the test but do not pay 1 Doom to the gamemaster.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ran4jfNQWID4anIi","name":"Master Alchemist","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have refined your measurements to the point of obsession, retesting established formulae, and making unique tools for weighing and separating the resins, fluids, pollens, dusts, and metals of your craft. When working with reagents on any petty enchantment that you have the Master of Formulae talent for, you may roll 1[CD]: if you roll an Effect, you have prevented the waste of much of the reagent. This only counts for one reagent: if multiple reagents are used, the rest are consumed as normal.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"58"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Alchemy","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Master of Formulae)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"rwkhle5cXwp3cHEv","name":"Catch the Wind","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You know the nuances of sailing, and can guide a vessel safely through difficult and dangerous situations. Decrease the Difficulty for any Sailing tests by one step per rank of Catch the Wind when you are piloting.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Sailing","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Navigation), Expertise(Sailing, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"s5TdPnWK6YkARy9j","name":"Master Crafter","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You work faster than lesser workers and have the vision to recognize alternative uses of common items. With success on a Challenging (D2) Craft test, you can adapt existing items at hand in order to solve a problem. This adaptation is only good for a single use. Any Momentum from the test can be spent to provide an additional use, 1 extra per point of Momentum. After the final use has been completed, the item is ruined for both the alternative use and its originally intended use. When you have access to your tools you gain bonus Momentum equal to your ranks in Master Smith, which may only be spent on reducing the time taken to complete the task.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"64"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Craft","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Journeyman), Expertise(Craft, 2)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"s7zdSCQjUfhJeWe5","name":"Indebted","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your family once had considerable wealth and privilege, but now has been reduced financially, either disenfranchised or otherwise stripped of a formerly reliable source of income. Your family’s holding, whether a manor house or keep, is now its sole source of income, discretely being sold piece by piece. While in your homeland during Downtime, you may make a Challenging (D2) Society roll to generate 1 Gold per Momentum earned, representing the distasteful necessity of selling of your family’s treasures. Unfortunately, any Complication rolled with this test reduces your Social Standing by 1, to a minimum of 0, and likely makes an enemy from within your family, angry at your reckless selling off of their inheritance.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"sCpTLFIqogPgD50N","name":"Just a Scratch","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have a knack for shrugging off injuries that would fell a lesser mortal. The amount of physical damage needed to inflict a Wound is increased by 1 per rank of Just a Scratch. For example, if you have Just a Scratch 1, you will suffer a Wound if 6 or more points of damage are inflicted, rather than the normal total of 5 or more.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"80"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Resistance","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Hardy)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":2},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"sIlCJ172J6cNoDSD","name":"Bureaucrat","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have moved through the halls of power for so long you have an intuitive grasp of how loyalties lie, flow, and change. Once per play session, you may make an Average (D1) Observation test. For each point of Momentum scored, you know the best means to make an approach to a single character, whether through flattery, bribery, threats, or other means, allowing you to turn one normal success rolled against them into a critical success </p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"0"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste()","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"styzjvYkrALMuwKS","name":"Ballistics","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have experience firing large and inaccurate weapons over long distances, and have learned the techniques that make these weapons truly effective. For each rank of Ballistics, you can reduce the Difficulty of a Warfare test to attack with a siege weapon by one step, to a minimum of Average (D1). Each rank of Ballistics also increases the damage of a siege weapon used by +1[CD].</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"90"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Warfare","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Artillerist)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"sw3Yfa5x4mbmewhR","name":"Hail of Arrows","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>When you attempt a ranged attack with a weapon with the Volley quality, you can spend 1 Load to use the Secondary Target Momentum spend for 1 Momentum (repeatable).</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"78"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Ranged Weapons","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Quick Release)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"t9CtWxVHngtQSJsA","name":"Heed My Words","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your bearing, presence, and voice grab attention and give enemies pause. This counts as a Display which must always use the Command skill. It has a range of Close, and inflicts 4[CD] mental damage with the Area and Stun qualities. This Display has no specific requirements, but it can only be used once in any scene. Outside of an action scene, you may instead add 1 point to Doom to seize the attention of a crowd of people and compel them to listen to you, though getting the crowd to do anything for you will still require Command or Persuade tests as normal. Toughened foes add one step of Difficulty to the Command test, and Nemesis foes add two steps.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"62"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Command","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Captain)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"tbeS8RKgu0DWIi6K","name":"Force of Presence","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Your damage bonus on mental attacks is increased by +1[CD].</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Persuade","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Persuade, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"uF137YMpBvFSrVwe","name":"Translator","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can read more languages than you can speak. For every Linguistics talent possessed, you can add one language that you can read with fluency. You do not count as fluent when hearing or speaking the language, though you can still communicate fluently through writing should you find a literate character to converse with.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"70"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Linguistics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Traveler's Tongue)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"uGOVc0pEGDU6RLrN","name":"Pugilist","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can add the Knockdown quality to all melee attacks.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"61"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Athletics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Might), Expertise(Athletics, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ubSUUlToF9g2zifJ","name":"Alchemist","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may re-roll one d20 when attempting an Alchemy test, but you must accept the new result. With this talent, you can also substitute Alchemy for ranged weapons when using an alchemical weapon.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"58"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Alchemy","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Alchemy, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ueBubFS336b9PUyi","name":"Wary","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have seen countless attempts at manipulation, and no longer trust easily. Whenever you are the target of a Persuade or Command action by another character or nonplayer character, any Momentum spent (or points added to Doom) to add bonus d20s to the Willpower test adds two dice instead of one, though the normal limit of three bonus d20s still applies. Further, if you resist the manipulation attempt, any other characters who have been convinced may each spend 1 Momentum (Immediate) to see through the manipulation, inspired by your example.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"66"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Discipline","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Jaded)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ujnPoktxk7cjbzlk","name":"Embittered","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have long since given up fealty to your lord. You avoid taxes and play fast-and-loose with the law. Within the borders of your homeland, your Social Standing is 0, and your Renown is reduced by 2 (to a minimum of -2). If you draw the attention of the authorities for any reason, all Command, Persuade, and Society tests increase in Difficulty by two steps. Whenever you spend Gold to Cultivate Renown during Carousing, you must spend two additional Gold, which don’t contribute [CD] to the attempt.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"20"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Caste","talentType":"caste","prerequisites":"Caste(Escaped Serf/Slave, Outcast)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vpmHjEvcw0qTTDXR","name":"Make your own Luck","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have little care for the vagaries of luck, and create your own advantages in life, whatever the cost or risk. You may spend 3 Momentum (Immediate) to gain the benefits of 1 Fortune point. Remember that Immediate Momentum spends can be paid for by adding to Doom instead of spending Momentum.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"90"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Fortune","talentType":"other","prerequisites":"","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"wXk09A799XLDuUdV","name":"Pantherish Twist","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may use your Acrobatics skill in place of Parry when attempting a Defend reaction, reducing the amount of Doom generated by 1, to a minimum of 0.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"56"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Acrobatics","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Nimble as a Cat)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"wkGZ6XeDzJtzwfo0","name":"Reflexive Block","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have become so attuned to your Parry skill that you may use your Parry skill when attempting a Defend Reaction against a ranged attack, which is normally not possible.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"75"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Parry","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Riposte)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"wpMMEGzh2WfsWfBn","name":"Strategist","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You are an experienced soldier that has fought in significant battles, skilled in assaulting and defending buildings. When crossing an obstacle or hindering terrain, or while skirting a hazard, you gain the benefit of Light Cover (2[CD] Cover Soak) from any ranged weapon attack, including siege weapons.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"91"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Warfare","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Warfare, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"xAib2RdC55DlUPE6","name":"Strife","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>With fractious nobles and near constant civil war, it pays to be attentive. Each day when in your homeland, you can make a free Simple (D0) Lore test. Each point of Momentum gives you a general idea as to whether there will be a major disturbance that day. While matters can take a turn at any point (and this doesn’t account for the actions of you or your allies) this test should provide accurate — if nonspecific — information about the general feel of the region.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"15"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Homeland","talentType":"homeland","prerequisites":"Homeland(Kush, Border Kingdom, Koth, Shem, Corinthia, The Black Kingdoms)","category":"","cost":0,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"xbMs0jYx3hbekYcv","name":"Know Your Enemy","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>When analyzing an opponent’s pattern of actions — including combats, social interactions, and rumors — you have learned to recognize your foe’s overall strategy. Once you have assembled the available clues, you may spend 1 Doom point. The gamemaster must then truthfully reveal your opponent’s short-term goals.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"72"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Lore","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Politically Savvy), Expertise(Lore, 2)","category":"","cost":400,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"xoHDwymzipwBHSbI","name":"Quiet Wisdom","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You may re-roll any dice that did not generate a success on the initial roll when making a Counsel test, but you must accept the new result.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"63"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Counsel","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Counsel, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"y4G0eJC9uSQnDaLd","name":"Witch","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Whether from dire sorcery or human cruelty, you have learned to discover when matters will escalate. Prior to any combat, you can attempt a Dire (D4) Insight test to gain an additional Standard Action. This Action takes place as if you had spent a Fortune point. Each additional rank of this talent beyond the first reduces the Insight test by one Difficulty step.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"69"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Insight","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sixth Sense)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"yDXDYtY9IAW43ZVA","name":"Eyes in the Forest","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have come to recognize when animals are reacting to the environment. Any time you are in the company of animals and need to make an Observation test, you may substitute the Animal Handling skill instead, if desired.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"59"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Animal Handling","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Born in the Saddle)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"z1EFiCr1UVgQgBXj","name":"Captain","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have learned to issue orders in such a way that they are clear to the recipient, with little margin for misinterpretation. You may re-roll one d20 when making a Command test, but you must accept the new result.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"61"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Command","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Command, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"zDimlK8Cc7W6Heb9","name":"Scout","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You can survey a new environment quickly. The first time you attempt an Observation test in a location you’ve never been before, you gain 1 bonus Momentum, which must be used on the Obtain Information Momentum spend.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"74"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Observation","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Sharp Senses)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"zb1Pnd2263rN08sW","name":"Scribe","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>You have had access to at least a small library of books, scrolls, or tablets, and gained a fascination with learning and knowledge. When rolling a Lore test you gain one bonus Momentum for every d20 that rolls less than your Lore Focus. This bonus Momentum can only be used for the Obtain Information Momentum spend.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"72"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Lore","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Expertise(Lore, 1)","category":"","cost":200,"rank":{"value":1,"max":3},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"zv7YbRqZ4r8d9hqZ","name":"Overcome Dark Powers","permission":{"default":0,"HPE2nGDuc5maUF0a":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><p>Truly wise counsellors know that while most traumas come from the mortal world, some come from more nefarious sources. When treating Trauma caused by Sorcery or a creature summoned by Sorcery, you may take on some of your patient’s burden. To do this, add 2 points to Doom and suffer a single Trauma. The patient then heals a single Trauma completely. You must heal your newly-gained Trauma as normal.</p></p>","source":{"book":"Core","page":"63"}},"skill":"undefined","tree":"Counsel","talentType":"skill","prerequisites":"Talent(Calming Oratory), Expertise(Counsel, 3)","category":"","cost":600,"rank":{"value":1,"max":1},"actionType":"","actionCategory":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/mc3e/assets/icons/compendiums/icon-talent-books.png","effects":[]}
